rite to NuttShell and sleep for a few hundred milliseconds to\nensure there is time for Nuttshell prompt appear again.\n\nArgs:\n    data (str): data to be passed on to Nuttshell.\n\nReturns:\n    None."]}, {"name": "pytest_embedded_nuttx.dut.NuttxDut.return_code", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "timeout", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Matches the 'echo $?' response and extracts the integer value\ncorresponding to the last program return code.\n\nThe first regex option on expect is for serial interface,\nwhile the second will match QEMU.\n\nReturns:\n    int: return code."]}, {"name": "pytest_embedded_nuttx.dut.NuttxDut.write_and_return", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "timeout", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "AnyStr", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.AnyStr", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Writes to Nuttshell and returns all available serial data until\nthe timeout.\nThis is useful when parsing and reusing the data is required, and\npexect is not enough.\n\nArgs:\n    data (str): data to be passed on to Nuttshell.\n    timeout (int): how long to wait for an answer in seconds.\n\nReturns:\n    AnyStr"]}, {"name": "pytest_embedded_nuttx.dut.NuttxDut.reset_to_nsh", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ready_prompt", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default"